From earlier tastes I retain a love of spacious, analogue‑feel remasters that preserve micro‑dynamics and transient snap; roomy, slightly ragged lead vocals with breathing space and character; tight, riff‑first guitars, punchy midrange and drums; layered multi‑tracked harmonies and tasteful organ accents; warm mastering with low compression, clear instrument separation and mixes that reveal studio detail on repeat.
Dislikes: hyper‑compressed or thin masters; raw lo‑fi textures that kill midrange warmth; vocals so drenched in reverb they lose attack or lyrics; harsh shouty singing; and production that overpolishes the sound and buries guitar grit or rhythmic drive.

